♪Give me fresh air♪

119
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:06,930
♪Let me breathe freely♪

120
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,310
♪Give me a pair of wings♪

121
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:12,590
♪Let me fly♪

122
00:06:13,260 --> 00:06:15,820
♪Thank you♪

123
00:06:16,330 --> 00:06:20,410
♪For encouraging me to move forward♪

124
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:25,300
♪There will always be♪

125
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:31,550
♪The most beautiful scenery ahead♪

126
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,520
She bit really hard, didn't she?

127
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,560
It's fine.

128
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,280
It's just a flesh wound.

129
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,160
That little girl's mom

130
00:06:45,310 --> 00:06:46,840
is the one who feels the greatest pain.

131
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,080
It's fine.

132
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,680
How cruel

133
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:54,080
can a person really be?

134
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,720
There is darkness in human nature.

135
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,600
We must face it.

136
00:06:59,110 --> 00:07:00,810
But every time something like this happens,

137
00:07:01,590 --> 00:07:02,840
it still weighs on my heart.

138
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,080
The darkness is bottomless.

139
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,540
But we must still believe in the light.

140
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,080
Just like Yu Weiwei.

141
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,000
Yes.

142
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,640
She will get better and better.

143
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:26,640
♪There will always be♪

144
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:32,840
♪The most beautiful scenery ahead♪

145
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,640
Is it okay to grill meat at home?

146
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,000
Won't the smell be too strong?

147
00:07:44,010 --> 00:07:44,920
It's fine.

148
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,880
Anyway, my parents went on vacation.

149
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,720
Wen they come back,
the smell will have dispersed.

150
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,600
When the cat's away,

151
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,960
the mice will play.

152
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:54,520
Or we could go out to eat.

153
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:56,080
Do you think your mom will be angry?

154
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,320
Don't spoil the fun.

155
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:01,120
I've been waiting for this hotpot and BBQ.

156
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:03,080
Finally, we've got to eat it.

157
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,960
They might come back and scold you.

158
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:06,110
Impossible.

159
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,400
Mrs. Lin wouldn't be that harsh.

160
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,480
She can't bear to do that.

161
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,840
Your parents are really close.

162
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,760
Not that close.

163
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,400
Take it.

164
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,880
- Tata.
- Cheers.

165
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:20,960
Why are you silent?

166
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,480
I'm hungry.

167
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,120
Dad.

168
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,080
Drinking tea?

169
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,600
Why are you out so late?

170
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,520
Where are you going?

171
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,520
I'm just throwing out the trash.

172
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,240
Throwing out the trash?

173
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,120
Wait a minute.

174
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,360
Here's more.

175
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,320
Throw this out too.

176
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:08,600
Okay.

177
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:10,800
Dad, after I throw out the trash,

178
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,160
I want to run for a bit.

179
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,680
You sleep first, don't wait for me.

180
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,960
When did my daughter

181
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,200
become so disciplined?

182
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,840
Well, I am your daughter after all.

183
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,440
I have to learn from you.

184
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,200
Don't you always say I'm too weak?

185
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,360
Shouldn't I be supposed to practice more?

186
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:29,560
See you, Dad.

187
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,720
Alright.

188
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,280
Tonight,

189
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:36,360
you don't need to run.

190
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,720
Tomorrow morning,

191
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,200
we'll start training

192
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:40,760
two hours earlier.

193
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:42,880
At 4:30 AM.

194
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,520
Be on time for exercises.

195
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:50,600
Go throw out the trash, then go to sleep.

196
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:04,160
Hello?

197
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,360
I can't make it.

198
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,160
Mr. Lin said training starts at

199
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,640
4:30 tomorrow morning.

200
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,320
If I find you guys now,

201
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,280
I'll need to rush back tonight.

202
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,360
It smells so good.

203
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,360
So delicious.

204
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,160
Can you guys stop being like this?

205
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:25,600
In my situation,

206
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:28,240
aren't you going to comfort me at all?

207
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:30,800
Just wait and see.

208
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:31,720
One day,

209
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:34,520
I'll escape from Mr. Lin's control.

210
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:35,760
Alright, alright.

211
00:10:35,770 --> 00:10:37,280
We'll wait for that day.

212
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,160
It smells so good.

213
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,760
How long until it's ready?

214
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:49,920
Soon. It's almost ready.

215
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,760
Soon.

216
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:51,720
I'll eat this first.

217
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,580
- Let's eat more for Wanru.
- This one's ready.

218
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:47,720
You're back.

219
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:51,840
It's already dawn.

220
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,080
What time is it?

221
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,680
It's almost 7:30.

222
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,120
You haven't had breakfast, right?

223
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,560
I made it for you yesterday.

224
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,600
I'll go heat it up for you.

225
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:11,380
(Emergency Response Training Base)

226
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:15,160
One, two, three!

227
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:22,840
Once we master it,

228
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,400
